<h2>As of September 2023, there have been over 860 BSides events around the world, hosted in 221 cities spanning 62 countries.</h2>
<h2><br />Through all of those events we have heard many success stories, talks given, projects launched, friendships made, careers accelerated, and much more.<br />Several years ago, we gathered comments for the “What BSides Means to Me” page on the wiki (<a href="/w/page/87930010/What%20BSides%20Means" search_id="undefined">http://www.securitybsides.com/w/page/87930010/What%20BSides%20Means</a>), now I would like to hear your BSides success stories and share them with the world.</h2>
<h2><br />Please send your BSides success stories to jack@bsides.org and we will add them to the new <a href="/BSides-Stories"><span old_style="color:#3366ff;">BSides stories</span></a> page.<br />We can’t wait to hear your BSides stories.</h2>

<h1><strong>What is BSides?</strong></h1>
<h3>Each BSides is a community-driven framework for building events&nbsp;for  and by information security community members.&nbsp; The goal is to expand  the spectrum of conversation beyond the traditional confines of space  and time.&nbsp; It creates opportunities for individuals to both present and  participate in an intimate atmosphere that encourages collaboration.&nbsp;It  is an intense event with discussions, demos, and interaction from  participants. It is where conversations for the next-big-thing are  happening.&nbsp;</h3>
&nbsp;
<h1><span old_style="color:#808080;">To see what BSides means to the community, check out the page:&nbsp;</span><a href="/w/page/87930010/What%20BSides%20Means"><span old_style="color:#339966;">What BSides Means to Me</span></a></h1>
<h2>&nbsp;</h2>
<h2><span old_style="font-family:'Segoe UI', 'Lucida Grande', Arial, sans-serif;font-size:17px;font-weight:bold;">Please send an email to </span><strong old_style="font-style:inherit;"><span old_style="color:#000000;">info@bsides.org</span></strong><span old_style="font-family:'Segoe UI', 'Lucida Grande', Arial, sans-serif;font-size:17px;font-weight:bold;"> if you would like to organize a BSides event in a city which is not already on the map. We will schedule a conversation to explain the rules and guidelines, and answer questions. Resources are available to help you make the event a success. You can see a brief overview of the ethos and rules on the </span><a old_style="font-family:'Segoe UI', 'Lucida Grande', Arial, sans-serif;font-size:17px;font-weight:bold;" href="/Guidelines">Guidelines</a><span old_style="font-family:'Segoe UI', 'Lucida Grande', Arial, sans-serif;font-size:17px;font-weight:bold;">&nbsp;page.&nbsp;</span></h2>

<p><strong old_style="font-family:'Segoe UI', 'Lucida Grande', Arial, sans-serif;font-size:17px;font-style:inherit;">BSides' History</strong></p>
<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<table class="proper" old_style="margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;text-align:center;width:90%;" border="0" width="878" align="center">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>
<p>BSides was born out of number of rejections to the CFP&nbsp;for Black Hat USA&nbsp;2009.&nbsp; A number of quality speakers were rejected, not due to lack of content but lack of space and time.&nbsp; Any constrained system must operate within the bounds to which it has defined itself.&nbsp; Conferences constrain themselves to the eight hours a day for however many days they run.&nbsp; Our goal is to provide people with options by removing those barriers and providing more alternatives for speakers, topics, and events.</p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<h2>Anti-spam policy</h2>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>It makes us all sad, but pointers to external pages from the front page will most likely be deleted without notice. Otherwise the page fills up rapidly with difficult-to-detect spam. Since version 2.0 of PBWiki, users can be authorized as '<em>Writer</em>s' or '<em>Readers</em>'. By default, new users are authorized as '<em>Writer</em>s', accounts conducting inadequate operations will be turned into '<em>Readers</em>' as a safety precaution. If the change appears unjustified, please contact&nbsp; the <a href="/SiteMaintainers">Site Maintainers</a> to restore the normal rights for the corresponding account.</p>
